# SilkLens — Trivy CVE / vulnerability allowlist
# =============================================================================
# Format:  <VULN-ID> [exp:<YYYY-MM-DD>]  # <reason>
#
# Rules:
#   - Every entry MUST have an inline comment explaining WHY it is suppressed.
#   - Use an expiry date (exp:) for time-limited suppressions (e.g. upstream
#     fix pending, grace period for a scheduled upgrade).
#   - Remove expired entries; they show up as parse warnings.
#
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
#
# Example entries (commented out):
#
#   # CVE-2023-12345 exp:2024-06-01  # Only exploitable via X; not reachable
#   #                                # through our API surface. Track: SILK-XXXX
#
#   # GHSA-xxxx-yyyy-zzzz            # False positive: affects feature Y which
#   #                                # we don't enable.
#
# =============================================================================
# No suppressions at this time.
# Add entries here when a specific CVE is confirmed non-exploitable or
# already mitigated at the infrastructure layer.
